abstract: The Upshot; analysts worry that patterns suggest future enrollment in state-run health exchange marketplaces may be sluggish; trend may indicate ongoing confusion about how Affordable Care Act works, or may presage further difficulty in getting people to sign up for health insurance.
lead_paragraph: The pattern so far suggests a challenge in reaching the goal of enrolling 10 million more eligible people within the next few years.

headline.main: Now the Hard Part: The Rate of Health Care Enrollment Seems Set to Slow
headline.print_headline: Analysts Fear That Health Care Enrollment Will Slow
